<subSubSection id="C337656CFF86FF90FD97FF44FDDD0F00" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9236E7FF86FF90FD97FF44FDDD0F00" blockId="35.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90FD97FF44FE8F0C90" bold="true" box="[199,328,367,392]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90FD97FF44FE850C90" bold="true" box="[199,322,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FF86FF90FC1FFF5BFDE50C90" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[335,546,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90FC1FFF5BFDE50C90" box="[335,546,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Aptilotella simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive in having a nearly straight posterior margin of the male sternite 5. The fore leg is boldly patterned in both sexes, and is strikingly similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FF86FF90F91BFFBFFB040CB4" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[1099,1219,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90F91BFFBFFB040CB4" box="[1099,1219,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FF86FF90F9AFFFBFFAAE0CB4" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[1279,1385,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladia">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90F9AFFFBFFAAE0CB4" box="[1279,1385,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. gladia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apterous limosinine 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FF86FF90FCDEFF93FCF20CC8" authority="Marshall" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2000" box="[398,821,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Myrmolimosina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90FCDEFF93FD070CC8" box="[398,704,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Myrmolimosina andersoni</emphasis>
Marshall
</taxonomicName>
and even a brachypterous 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FF86FF90F9C2FF93FB3B0CC8" authorityName="Richards" authorityYear="1951" box="[1170,1276,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aluligera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FF86FF90F9C2FF93FB3B0CC8" box="[1170,1276,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Aluligera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B16FF86FF90FDCEFFF7FE900CED" author="Richards, O. W." box="[158,343,476,501]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="296 - 301" refId="ref49791" refString="Richards, O. W. (1955) Contributions a l'etude de la faune entomologique du Ruanda-Urundi (Mission P. Basilewsky 1953). XXXI. Diptera Sphaeroceridae. Annales du Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale - Tervuren, Belgique, Serie in- 8 °, Sciences Zoologiques, 36, 296 - 301." type="journal article" year="1955">Richards, 1955</bibRefCitation>
). Field observations could yield insight into the potential behavioural functions of these remarkably convergent fore limbs.
</paragraph>
